MLObjective and loss function

What is ML Objective?
ML Objective means formalised goal that training process aim to acheive 

What is ML Objective in  Gmail Smart compose?

The ML objective in Smart compose is next token prediction. 
For ex: After i write: "I hope you are -  ", then it predicts "doing" 

Text Generation tasks next token prediction is well suited. Because 
system incrementally generating new text by predicting the next token
until EOS token is reached 

Why we need loss function?
This is going to optimise the model for correctly predicting the 
next token 
This measure the difference bewteen expected output and generated output 
This loss updates the model parameters to produce more accurate probabilities in the future

How model computes loss?

Suppose in a sentence "How Are you", model computes 
loss of each token, How, Are and You in parallel.
This is going to speed up training process by computing loss of all
tokens 
